  ('atlantic-hurricane-season-frame', 'caribbean', '11C', '{"tropical","liveaboard","romance"}', '{"stay","activities"}', 'lookahead', 'lookahead', 'Atlantic hurricane season — the honest, reassuring frame', 'Season runs Jun 1–Nov 30, but most major-hurricane activity is Aug–Oct (peak around mid-September). Most of the season, most places are doing exactly what you came for. And it''s never an ambush — systems are tracked days out, with warnings well ahead. Read the season, travel it wisely.', null, null, null, '{"months":[6,7,8,9,10,11]}'::jsonb, 'Jun 1–Nov 30; peak mid-Aug–mid-Oct', 'curated', 80, null, null),
  ('tci-hurricane-aware', 'turks-caicos', '11C', '{"tropical","liveaboard"}', '{"stay","activities"}', 'lookahead', 'lookahead', 'Turks & Caicos — hurricane-season straight talk', 'Our home waters, straight: T&C sits in the Atlantic corridor, so respect the Aug–Oct peak and plan a little. The flip side — the rest of the year is glorious, Grace Bay calm is the norm, and you''ll have days of warning if anything brews. Travel the shoulder months, protect your trip when you book, and you travel it like the locals: relaxed and ready.', null, null, null, '{"months":[8,9,10]}'::jsonb, 'respect Aug–Oct; relish the rest', 'curated', 80, null, null),
  ('southern-caribbean-below-belt', 'southern-caribbean', '11C', '{"tropical","liveaboard"}', '{"stay","activities"}', 'lookahead', 'lookahead', 'Southern Caribbean (Aruba/Bonaire/Curaçao) — below the hurricane belt', 'Happy geography: the ABC islands plus Trinidad & Tobago sit far enough south that most Atlantic storms pass to the north — widely known as below the hurricane belt, the lowest-risk corner of the Caribbean. Lower-risk isn''t no-risk, but for warm water with the calmest odds, the southern islands are a smart, sunny choice nearly year-round.', null, null, null, null, 'lowest-risk Caribbean zone, near year-round', 'curated', 70, null, null),
